articles.description: Members of the Michigan State faculty voted 61-4 to express no confidence in the eight-member governing body at the university. Meanwhile, the institution's interim president wrote to the campus community about cooperation with ongoing investigations.
articles.headline: Michigan State faculty delivers no-confidence vote on board of trustees

images.caption: The Michigan State faculty's vote against the board of trustees came largely in response to the board's decision to name John Engler the school's interim president.
images.name: John Engler [600x400] - Copy (2)

images.caption: Michigan State students, including one who jumped onto and sat on the middle of a table, interrupt an MSU board of trustees meeting to protest the school's selection of John Engler as the interim president.
images.name: MSU students vent frustration over interim president selection

videos.description: Thomas Dziagwa and Jeffrey Carroll hit 3-pointers in transition for the Cowboys in the first half.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State drills back-to-back triples

videos.description: Yankuba Sima intercepts the ball then speeds down the court for an easy layup and draws the foul.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State's Sima steals for a chance at a 3-point play

videos.description: Kendall Smith misses the layup but gets it back and finds Brandon Averette on the outside who buries a triple to extend Oklahoma State's lead 34-23.
videos.headline: Cowboys' Averette keeps it alive for 3-pointer

videos.description: Norense Odiase swats the ball away from Kendall Smith with one second left on the shot clock in the second half.
videos.headline: Texas Tech's Odiase makes crucial defensive play

videos.description: Brandone Francis turns around in midair to find Jarrett Culver and Culver knocks down a 3-pointer from the right wing.
videos.headline: Texas Tech's Francis makes nifty dish to Culver for 3

videos.description: Keenan Evans feeds Jarrett Culver who powers in a one-handed dunk for a new career-high of 22 points against Oklahoma State.
videos.headline: Culver throws down the hammer for Texas Tech

videos.description: The Red Raiders rally in the second half to beat the Cowboys 75-70 on Tuesday night.
videos.headline: No. 14 Texas Tech hangs on against Oklahoma State
